For the one toxic covered process, the ammonia refrigeration process, all of the alternative release scenarios would be equivalent to a release from a small hole (1/4" diameter) in a tank or pipe containing ammonia at the highest system pressure.  At the Kingman facility, a release of this type would result in a maximum downwind distance of about 0.2 miles, or 1,060 feet.  To determine this distance, we used the EPA's "Risk Management Program Guidance for Ammonia Refrigeration."

